column5: Travelling on Cook's is still very good, However a LOT more snow than last weekend!!!  Roaches Point  You will  find 5-6" of Ice. Pumphouse and the Fingers  8"  Bikes and Sleds travelling with no problems,  No Slush or cracks.  Lots of Fish being caught,  This will likely be the Last busy weekend in Gilford,  By next weekend Innisfil and North should be Good to Go!!!  Rick
Thanks for the info Rick
Yeah, thanks Rick!  Can't wait for Innisfil to be ready. It's my best shot at my first Whitey 'cause I'm a walker too. Like T-Bay, 5 mile walks aren't in the cards for me this year....
ill be there this weekend looking for laker and whities...very carefully...lol

planning to be out with Pikeie and a buddy before he goes back to Soo for school on Sunday . Most likely Gilford as I'm not sure Innisfil park ice is safe yet .Any on eknow for sure ?  Be walkin and will keep an eye out we have a OFC sticker on our bucket !  TB
Long range forecast is calling for unseasonably warm weather NEXT weekend. I'm still defrosting over last Saturdays outing so will wait it out!
You mean,I can get the golf clubs back out? LOL

Well I sure hope they're right... considering they're showing -32C for next Thursday here and -38C in Temagami where I planned on heading! Don't sound warm to me.... and Friday is showing -35C. Sure ain't ice fishin weather.
I couldn't find any warm weather in the long range   look for me out from gilford rd with my skidoo and hut satuday morning

I'm heading to AC/DC right now, so I'm thinking of sleeping in tomorrow & heading out Sunday morning.  I'll see how I feel when I get home, but after working outside all week, I'm pretty zonked. I'll check in tonight...good luck to those heading out! If I head up in the morning, I'll look for you Terry...
AC/DC! You lucky guy awesome , saw them at SARS fest , they kicked the Stones butt , best show I had seen in a long time .they truly seem to enjoy what they do .  TB
LOL, now that's a good "line"
Shouldnt you be sleeping bud?  Have a great day on the hard water Terry. I,ll see ya out there soon enough my friend.
He's not that old yet Brian... I think he's good 'till 9:15 or so....
Hey     ten      LOL
LOL       I was         Waiting for the           Hang 10               LOL
LOL
Hahaha, nope! Sunday's gonna be the day for me. Way too wired right now....  Have fun, be safe & good luck to all!
well I had some mechanical problems and a lock froze to my hand when I grabbed it so I wasn't ready to go till 9 and by then I lost all ambition so looks like I am out sunday instead
Just a wee bit Cold eh Terry... Good thing I'm going tomorrow...
you got that right..dang cold
well it was about -22 early this morning 6am plus wind chill now about -15
You are getting old... aren't ya!    Mind you that -29C.. having to put your ATV in Ron's trailer to preheat, etc, last year wasn't much fun either....

was out today just got back..i was looking for your machine terry and hut but did not see it in cooks bay..i fished just off of snake island and got 2 whitefish..i was in 61 feet of water and ice was 4- 6 inchs of black ice ...i did take my skidoo out there and checked out ice all the way up to snake island from cooks bay...found some slush spots but nothing serious... finnally a whitefish on the ice....i drove up closer to fox about 73 feet of water ice was 4-6 inches in that area not all black ice so i decided to stop and stay were i was for the rest of the morning....

So who is going where, seems lots of us have been out there but I haven't seen any other OFNers I will be out somewhere I don't think most places for whitefish/trout are ready and BP will be a zoo with no parking so cooks I will be out Saturday morning, with my hut and skidoo, I should be easy to see, wave me down I can help move people out too I will be parking on gilford rd last sunday I got to try out the new (to me) skidoo go out on cooks bay had to keep moving to find perch didn't get a lot of them but took enough home for a good meal of them heres my machine with the quickie auger mount I made I am now ready for some heavy duty fishing this guy over from me seemed to be in the bag LOL
LMAO! That has to be best redneck portable Ive seen.

I'm thinking about getting out to cooks this weekend, depends on the snow Saturday (might go later in the day if it stops early) and the cold Sunday (won't forget the mr buddy heater this time).  Lexxington and I went out last week from Gillford road and got into a few but not loads.  If anyone wants to meet up I'm in (on foot however so no 5 mile walks please   )
Thats BUBBLE BOY.LOL
Terry what are you doing tomorrow Friday i'll be hitting Cooks Bay friday and saturday with a few OFC members on saturday.
I believe my bro memart is heading out with our pop. I can just see him now, with that brand new gas auger. He,ll be drill,n and drill,n and not fish,n. Just like a guy with a new bass boat.LOL
I thought I would work tomorrow....LOL...... like I want to  but am good to go on Saturday
lol I fished with Rob last weekend and your son as well. Rob only drilled a few holes and your son has a swing at it as well.  You should come out Saturday B
Ok Terry i'll see you saturday i'll be with a few of the guys off the board
Nice rig! Hopefully you'll have better luck with your machine than our OFC friend up in Dryden.  BTW I thought you said you met no OFC'rs? The guy with the plastic bag had to be Clamp-it  .
LOL you might be right
It,s cold outside Pauly.
I wish I could join you Terry, but its my turn to be on call this weekend so I'd better not stray too far. The rig looks great, how did she run?
my turn to be on call too I am taking my phone with me....they can wait...LOL
I think we're going to try and head up to Cook's this weekend Terry.  Paul's on nights so Sunday will probably be the day.  I'll let you know for sure as the day gets closer.  Joey
@ this moment im LAUGHING MY ASS OFF!!!!  BUBBLE BOY FISH'S!!!  darn thats funny!  whats holding the bag into place!!??!?!?!?!!?!?!??!??!?!?!?!  nice equipement BTW!
It's never to cold to do some fishing. I bet if it was some hunting you would.
Hey Jose let me know where your going and we will meet up  Rob
Do you know how warm a 12 gauge barrel feels after you shoot it off? LOL  Be vewy vewy qwiet,it,s wabbit season.

I was out last friday and saturday from gilford. Did pretty well on friday probably caught atleast fifty from day break till 11:30 nothing huge but kept 22 between 8-10 inches. Saturday went back out to the same spot with no luck first thing, had to move around alot after trying about 8 spots settled in 24 fow and got into some decent action fished until 10 and ended up catching around 30 fish and ended up keeping ten. I think i'll hit innisfil park this weekend for some perch and hopefully a rogue whitefish...lol

I'm heading out from Gilford on Saturday for the first ice fish of '09.  So far, I'm flying solo, but if anyone wants to meet up in the am, PM me. I'll be on the lookout for you, Terry, & any other OFC'ers.  Timmies at 400/Major Mack is always a good meeting spot.
Hey Bill i'll be heading up in the am as well.
I'm going to decide what time to head up a little later tonight. I want to see what the weather's gonna do.
OOOHHH!  Been a while Bill..  You don't call anymore and you havn't brought me flowers or even a card in ages..    cherish the love and all that jazz!!  HD
Yeah, it HAS been a while, Fidel!  We should get the stars to line up & get on the ice again...let me know your schedule. I have every other weekend to do whatever.
